<h2 id='ruby_example'>Ruby example of making call</h2>
<p>Easiest way to get data from Slim APi is using <code>curb</code>. It is ruby binding of <code>curl</code></p>

<pre><code class="ruby">#Â $ gem install curb
require 'curb'

# Get data from api
c = Curl.get("http://silver.local:9393/v1/<%= @taxonomy %>/clients") do |curl| 
  curl.headers["Api-Token"] = "<%= @api_access.api_token %>"
  curl.headers["Content-Type"] = "application/json"
end
puts c.body_str

# Get data from api with specified ID
c = Curl.get("http://silver.local:9393/v1/<%= @taxonomy %>/clients", :id => 3923) do |curl| 
  curl.headers["Api-Token"] = "<%= @api_access.api_token %>"
  curl.headers["Content-Type"] = "application/json"
end
puts c.body_str

